    "Body": " nmx.art is looking for a Blockchain Solution Architect to join our team and work on exciting blockchain solutions. The Blockchain Solution Architect will be responsible for the architecture and implementation of solutions for critical systems using open source stack. This position is a hands-on, self-directed design and development of highly scalable, reliable, and performance efficient applications. The successful candidate should have a thorough knowledge and hands-on experience in all levels of Software Development Life Cycle. The Blockchain Solution Architect will be reporting directly to the Product Manager. Preferred Qualifications: Computer Science degree with 7+ years of experience in software development (full stack), including design, implementation, debugging, and support (minimum 2 years as Solution Architect or Team Lead / Senior Developer, 1+ years experience in Blockchain). Experience developing a real-world solution using Ethereum public network. Understanding of different blockchain frameworks (Hyperledger Fabric, Hyperledger Sawtooth, Corda, and others). Understand Blockchain Data Architecture and ability to identify/recommend ways to optimize data elements on-chain/off-chain. Experience building complex applications. Strong proficiency in developing software solutions with deep experience in one or more relevant languages (Node.js, Go, Python). Experience using multiple frameworks (Angular, React, Vue, React Native, Flutter, and others). Extensive experience designing, maintaining and integrating 3rd party APIs. Experience with SQL and NoSQL database servers, JSON schemas and related technologies (Postgres, Mysql, MongoDB, CouchDB or others). Proven track record of delivering high quality software solutions on time. Possesses strong analytical skills, with excellent problem-solving abilities in the face of ambiguity. Experience designing and building highly-scaled distributed systems and web services. Very strong computer science fundamentals in algorithm design, data structures, problem solving, and complexity analysis. Experience in enterprise software or cloud services. Understanding of version control (Git) and code documentation. Great verbal and written communication skills. Bonus: Understand the principles of cloud native architecture Experience in writing smart contracts for multiple blockchain frameworks such as Hyperledger Fabric, Hyperledger Sawtooth, Ethereum, and Corda. Experience developing Dapps using Truffle Framework. Proficiency testing distributed systems. Good understanding of various different consensus algorithms used. Experience with containerization and orchestration using Docker & Kubernetes. Conversant with security best practices Responsibilities: Acting as a technical subject matter expert and draw from your extensive technical experience to help your team with architectural, design and technology stack selection when kicking off new projects. Configure and maintain application servers and processes, including monitoring of system health and performance, to ensure high levels of performance, availability, and security. Independently analyze, solve, and correct issues in real time, providing problem resolution end-to-end. Create technical documentation including functional and technical designs, and define business and application migration rules. Perform software quality assurance checks, which includes testing and validating the solutions deliver on requirements. Prepare training content & mentor team members, provide training on technologies. ? Goals: Drive project initiation, scoping, and planning. Maintain the release schedule. Collaboratively define blockchain systems architecture and best practices. Document best practices and act as a knowledgeable resource for blockchain engineering and problem-solving. Provide technical expertise across all areas of the build, release, and operations. ", 
